llItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"5740fe10-013e-52cb-9a0b-1454f5b5b57f","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"cd94d14b-e3eb-5546-b8d3-204aa49e20b0","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"f1db6f6c-0f56-54cb-97b1-cbf1ffd6ea4d","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"b4066bd7-f523-564e-a912-850420dc51d2","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"cd306277-b91d-5ce4-a493-65909dcf045e","slug":"causes","fullItemName":"Causes"}]},{"id":"14ff8a9f-d9e8-501c-8534-2e32a5e4a1fa","fullItemName":"Diagnosis","slug":"diagnosis","subChapters":[{"id":"497989ed-88f6-5499-99a3-18e8a3225bdc","slug":"assessment","fullItemName":"Assessment"}]},{"id":"7cc490a8-0474-5fe7-bc44-9cf3996a4c33","fullItemName":"Management","slug":"management","subChapters":[{"id":"59fa17d7-bf9a-58d3-84c6-22816a3015cf","slug":"skin-lump","fullItemName":"Scenario: Skin lump"},{"id":"58e7fdb7-41cd-5c9a-8776-1229a3ad4eed","slug":"lymphadenopathy","fullItemName":"Scenario: Lymphadenopathy"},{"id":"afc8611d-187d-57b6-89c2-807486576600","slug":"thyroid-lump","fullItemName":"Scenario: Thyroid lump"},{"id":"1117f2a6-53a8-5b0d-8bda-45aa883a0b68","slug":"salivary-gland-lump","fullItemName":"Scenario: Salivary gland lump"},{"id":"6c8c6bf1-a425-59a0-8e2d-2b72c6ab1b41","slug":"congenital-or-developmental-lump","fullItemName":"Scenario: Congenital or developmental lump"},{"id":"b1059bc8-89eb-51ce-bd6e-bc538a290e04","slug":"carotid-lump","fullItemName":"Scenario: Carotid lump"},{"id":"0cc73f60-bbd1-5870-857c-3c8adf30dcec","slug":"unknown-cause","fullItemName":"Scenario: Unknown cause"}]},{"id":"b7c0809f-89c5-53bd-a7b1-8a88d626ce22","fullItemName":"Supporting evidence","slug":"supporting-evidence","subChapters":[]},{"id":"70a5ec8b-a5e2-51fb-8d4a-48bb8ebdacf0","fullItemName":"How this topic was developed","slug":"how-this-topic-was-developed","subChapters":[{"id":"b41e81b3-902e-519d-a104-436978f1167a","slug":"search-strategy","fullItemName":"Search strategy"},{"id":"a93899d0-0843-5ecf-92e9-b271d2fc8d26","slug":"stakeholder-engagement","fullItemName":"Stakeholder engagement"},{"id":"2a3cf512-59ff-576c-9560-44565ac3a9ff","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria"},{"id":"bbfe4358-ff9d-5fe7-b9fc-aafa1bf965b4","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers"},{"id":"6043633a-ac01-5d95-94c6-343802922275","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"c5d40903-c5aa-53af-9f74-cc0f6ea353f8","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"7cc490a8-0474-5fe7-bc44-9cf3996a4c33","slug":"management","fullItemName":"Management"},"subChapters":[{"id":"87b16620-642f-5bec-91b0-61800be3ba71","slug":"management-of-a-salivary-gland-lump","fullItemName":"Management of a salivary gland lump","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 474f6661-ebac-4e0d-a66a-0f63476c5c5d --><h3>Management of a salivary gland lump</h3><!-- end field 474f6661-ebac-4e0d-a66a-0f63476c5c5d -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item f07bc727-3bf1-45c6-8202-27484b6e5608 --><!-- begin field dff730f8-3b15-4f7e-87ac-49b192122880 --><ul><li><strong>If there is a parotid or submandibular gland swelling </strong>that is persistent and/or unexplained:<ul><li>Arrange urgent referral (for an appointment within 2 weeks) to an ear, nose, and throat surgeon.</li></ul></li><li><strong>If there is a suspected <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/neck-lump/background-information/causes/#salivary-gland-lumps\">salivary gland calculus</a>:</strong><ul><li>Arrange referral to an ear, nose, and throat surgeon or maxillofacial surgeon, depending on local service provision, the urgency depending on clinical judgement.</li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field dff730f8-3b15-4f7e-87ac-49b192122880 --><!-- end item f07bc727-3bf1-45c6-8202-27484b6e5608 -->","subChapters":[{"id":"15d1dbae-ed9b-57c5-8f55-ed37b3c392b2","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-c88","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":4,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 2894eedf-5f61-4d1b-b62b-ae3b98db9153 --><h4>Basis for recommendation</h4><!-- end field 2894eedf-5f61-4d1b-b62b-ae3b98db9153 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item c88139ab-6cc6-464d-8003-b1f06bd36c3e --><!-- begin field 2a92a6ab-78ad-4a57-ad66-538ab5530d90 --><p>The recommendations on management of salivary gland swellings are based on the UK publication <em>Management of salivary gland tumours: United Kingdom national multidisciplinary guidelines</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/neck-lump/references/\">Sood, 2016</a>] and expert opinion in review articles on salivary gland disorders [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/neck-lump/references/\">Wilson, 2014</a>] and on salivary gland tumours [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/neck-lump/references/\">Mantravadi, 2019</a>].</p><h5>Management of persistent or unexplained salivary gland swelling</h5><ul><li>This recommendation is largely based on the UK publication on the management of salivary gland tumours, which recommends referral to a rapid access neck lump clinic if there is suspected malignancy. Additional investigations may include ultrasound-guided fine-needle aspiration cytology (FNAC) and core biopsy before possible surgical intervention [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/neck-lump/references/\">Sood, 2016</a>].</li><li>This approach is supported by expert opinion in a review article, which notes that surgery is the most common initial treatment for salivary gland tumours, the extent of surgery depending on the tumour location, histology, and degree of local invasion [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/neck-lump/references/\">Mantravadi, 2019</a>]. Expert opinion in an additional review article recommends urgent referral if there is suspected salivary gland malignancy [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/neck-lump/references/\">Wilson, 2014</a>].</li></ul><h5>Management of suspected salivary gland calculi</h5><ul><li>This recommendation is based on expert opinion in a review article, which states that additional investigation such as salivary gland ultrasound or CT may show a stone or dilated duct, and eventual surgical removal of the stone or salivary gland excision may be needed, depending on the location of the stone [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/neck-lump/references/\">Wilson, 2014</a>]. This recommendation is supported by the expert opinion of previous external reviewers of this CKS topic.</li></ul><!-- end field 2a92a6ab-78ad-4a57-ad66-538ab5530d90 --><!-- end item c88139ab-6cc6-464d-8003-b1f06bd36c3e -->","subChapters":[]}]}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3666801979"]}